revision.text:
{{Infobox summit | summit_name = Arab League 21st summit | other_titles = | image = | date = 30–31 March 2009 | country = Mauritania | cities = [[Doha]] | follows = [[2010 Arab League summit]] | precedes = [[2008 Arab League summit]] | website = }}
The '''2009 Arab League summit''' was held in [[Doha]], [[Qatar]] on March 30, 2009. The Arab League defied the [[International Criminal Court]] by giving a "warm welcome" to [[Sudanese President]] [[Omar Hassan al-Bashir]], whom the Court placed a warrant on for war crimes in the [[Darfur genocide]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/03/29/AR2009032902507.html | work=The Washington Post | first=Brian | last=Murphy | title=Sudan's Leader Arrives in Qatar | date=March 30, 2009}}</ref>
==Reactions== [[President of Egypt|Egyptian President]] [[Hosni Mubarak]] boycotted the summit amid differences with Qatar stemming from the [[2008–2009 Israel–Gaza conflict]].<ref>{{cite news|title=What is behind Egyptian President Mubarak's absence from Arab Summit?|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-03/29/content_11096352.htm|author=Hu Dandan and Liao Zhenyun|publisher=[[Xinhua]]|date=|accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref> Other Arab countries like Saudi Arabia were also hesitant to come to the summit if Iran or Hamas were in attendance (neither of the parties came while the Saudis did).{{citation needed|date=January 2014}}
==Incidents== After [[Sheikh Hamad bin Khalifa Al Thani]] speech, [[Libyan]] leader [[Muammar al-Gaddafi]] called [[King Abdullah of Saudi Arabia]] a liar, accusing him of "bringing the Americans to occupy Iraq" and of being "made by Britain and protected by the US.", while stating: "I am an international leader, the dean of the Arab rulers, the king of kings of Africa and the imam (leader) of Muslims, and my international status does not allow me to descend to a lower level".<ref>{{cite news|title=Muammar Gaddafi accuses Saudi Arabia's King Abdullah of lying at Arab summit|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/qatar/5079290/Muammar-Gaddafi-accuses-Saudi-Arabias-King-Abdullah-of-lying-at-Arab-summit.html|author=Adel Darwish|publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=March 30, 2009|accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Libya's Gadhafi storms out of Arab summit|url=http://www.ndtv.com/article/world/libya-s-gadhafi-storms-out-of-arab-summit-344|publisher=[[NDTV]] ([[Associated Press]])|date=March 30, 2009|accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref> He then invited the King to visit him to solve the issues between the two.<ref>{{cite web|title=''Libya's Kadhafi hurls apologies to Saudi king'' |url=http://www.france24.com/en/20090330-libyas-kadhafi-hurls-insults-saudi-king |work= |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5hlQa00n2?url=http://www.france24.com/en/20090330-libyas-kadhafi-hurls-insults-saudi-king |archivedate=June 24, 2009 |deadurl=no |accessdate=June 21, 2009 |df=mdy }}</ref>
